s a construction business in the s it shut down its construction activities in the s and switched to publishing it is the largest education company and the largest book publisher in the world pearson has a primary listing on the london stock exchange and is a constituent of the ftse  index it has a secondary listing on the new york stock exchange in the form of american depository receipts  strand shell mex house in london the headquarters of pearson contents  history  construction business  to the s  publishing business s to    to    to    to   operations  criticism  united kingdom  libyan investment authority  tax avoidance  references  external links historyedit construction business  to the sedit the company was founded by samuel pearson in  as a building and engineering concern operating in yorkshire under the name s pearson  son in  control passed to his grandson weetman dickinson pearson an engineer who in  moved the business to london and turned it into one of the worlds largest construction companies another of its prominent engineers was ernest william moir who after working for pearson on tunnels in new york city became the contractors agent on construction of the blackwall tunnel under the river thames in london between  and  the company also built the admiralty harbour at dover the halifax dry dock in canada the east river railway tunnels in new york city the mexican grand canal that drained mexico city the tehuantepec railway in mexico and railways and harbours around the world in november  the firm began construction of hm factory gretna the largest cordite factory in the uk during world war i the construction business was shut down in the s among its final projects was completion of the sennar dam in sudan in  publishing business s to edit in  the firm acquired a  stake in the london branch of merchant bankers lazard brothers an interest which was increased to  in  during the depression years pearson continued to hold a  stake until  in  pearson purchased a number of local daily and weekly newspapers in the united kingdom which it combined to form the westminster press group in  it bought the financial times and acquired a  stake in the economist it purchased the publisher longman in  the company was first listed on the london stock exchange in  it went on to buy paperback publisher penguin in  and in  childrens imprint ladybird books in  pearson invested in the british satellite broadcasting consortium which a few years later merged with sky tv to form a new company british sky broadcasting bskyb  to edit during the s pearson acquired a number of tv production and broadcasting assets including former itv franchisee thames television and sold most of its nonmedia assets under the leadership of future us congressman bob turner westminster press was sold to newsquest in  pearson acquired the education division of harpercollins in  from news corporation  and acquired book publishers scott foresman  co in  in  pearson acquired prentice hall textbookssimon  schuster trade books from viacom and merged it with its own education unit addisonwesley longman to form pearson education  to edit pearson acquired dorling kindersley the illustrated reference publisher and integrated it within penguin in march  and then bought acquired national computer systems ncs in september  so entering the educational assessment and school management systems market in the united states in  pearson sold its  stake in rtl group for  billion euros and then purchased rough guides the travel publisher and brought it under penguin pearson acquired edexcel a provider of qualifications in the uk in  and acquired about  stake in meximerica media inc for  million for the swelling us hispanic market in  pearson purchased a series of other testing and assessment businesses including knowledge technologies in  ags in  and national evaluation systems and promissor in  pearson acquired national evaluation systems a provider of customised state assessment