as a construction business in the s it shut down its construction activities in the s and switched to publishing it is the largest education company and the largest book publisher in the world pearson has a primary listing on the london stock exchange and is a constituent of the ftse  index it has a secondary listing on the new york stock exchange in the form of american depository receipts  strand shell mex house in london the headquarters of pearson contents  history  construction business  to the s  publishing business s to    to    to    to   operations  criticism  united kingdom  libyan investment authority  tax avoidance  references  external links historyedit construction business  to the sedit the company was founded by samuel pearson in  as a building and engineering concern operating in yorkshire under the name s pearson  son in  control passed to his grandson weetman dickinson pearson an engineer who in  moved the business to london and turned it into one of the worlds largest construction companies another of its prominent engineers was ernest william moir who after working for pearson on tunnels in new york city became the contractors agent on construction of the blackwall tunnel under the river thames in london between  and  the company also built the admiralty harbour at dover the halifax dry dock in canada the east river railway tunnels in new york city the mexican grand canal that drained mexico city the tehuantepec railway in mexico and railways and harbours around the world in november  the firm began construction of hm factory gretna the largest cordite factory in the uk during world war i the construction business was shut down in the s among its final projects was completion of the sennar dam in sudan in  publishing business s to edit in  the firm acquired a  stake in the london branch of merchant bankers lazard brothers an interest which was increased to  in  during the depression years pearson continued to hold a  stake until  in  pearson purchased a number of local daily and weekly newspapers in the united kingdom which it combined to form the westminster press group in  it bought the financial times and acquired a  stake in the economist it purchased the publisher longman in  the company was first listed on the london stock exchange in  it went on to buy paperback publisher penguin in  and in  childrens imprint ladybird books in  pearson invested in the british satellite broadcasting consortium which a few years later merged with sky tv to form a new company british sky broadcasting bskyb  to edit during the s pearson acquired a number of tv production and broadcasting assets including former itv franchisee thames television and sold most of its nonmedia assets under the leadership of future us congressman bob turner westminster press was sold to newsquest in  pearson acquired the education division of harpercollins in  from news corporation  and acquired book publishers scott foresman  co in  in  pearson acquired prentice hall textbookssimon  schuster trade books from viacom and merged it with its own education unit addisonwesley longman to form pearson education  to edit pearson acquired dorling kindersley the illustrated reference publisher and integrated it within penguin in march  and then bought acquired national computer systems ncs in september  so entering the educational assessment and school management systems market in the united states in  pearson sold its  stake in rtl group for  billion euros and then purchased rough guides the travel publisher and brought it under penguin pearson acquired edexcel a provider of qualifications in the uk in  and acquired about  stake in meximerica media inc for  million for the swelling us hispanic market in  pearson purchased a series of other testing and assessment businesses including knowledge technologies in  ags in  and national evaluation systems and promissor in  pearson acquired national evaluation systems a provider of customised state assessments for teacher certification in the us in april  and announced that it had agreed to acquire harcourt assessment and harcourt education international from reed elsevier for m in cash in may  pearson then completed the acquisition of harcourt assessment merging the acquired businesses into pearson assessment  information pearson also acquired ecollege a digital learning technology group for m in may  in february  pearson announced the sale of its pearson data management division formerly the scanner manufacturing and servicing division of ncs inc to scantron corporation part of mf worldwide which had been its main competitor pearson acquired wall street english for m in  and bought the school learning systems division of sistema educacional brasileiro seb for m in  also in  pearson sold its  stake in interactive data to investment funds managed by silver lake partners and warburg pincus for  billion  to edit in july  pearson announced the creation of pearson college a british degree provider based in london also in  pearson acquired connections education and agreed to sell its  stake in ftse international limited to the london stock exchange for £ million in  pearson also increased its stake in tutorvista such that it had a  stake for  million pearson entered into talks with rival conglomerate bertelsmann over the possibility of combining their respective publishing companies penguin group and random house in october  the houses are considered two of the big six publishing companies on  october  pearson said it would merge penguin books with bertelsmanns random house to create the worlds biggest consumer book publisher then in may  pearson announced its acquisition of globalenglish corporation an american business english software and solutions company in an allcash transaction in may  pearson announced a new restructuring plan to invest in digital learning and emerging markets after predicting weaker earnings the change supports the decoupling of the penguin consumer publishing business into a separate entity with random house forming penguin random house the new structure combines the separate education companies pearson international and pearson north america under one pearson company pearson will organize around three global lines of business – school higher education and professional the financial times group and pearson english will form part of pearson professional in july  pearson announced it had cut  jobs representing  of the companys workforce pearson announced on  july  that it had agreed to sell the ft group which includes business daily financial times to japanese media group nikkei for £ million or  billion the sale does not include ft groups london property at one southwark bridge in august  pearsons sold its  stake in the economist to the agnelli family for £ million who previously held  of the group the remaining  of the economist group is owned by the schroders cadburys and the rothschilds on  november  pearson announced it was rebranding including creating a new logo with a  focus on education on  july  indiabased education technology company byjus acquired tutor vista and edurite from pearson on  july  pearson agreed to reduce its holding in penguin random house to  by selling a a  stake in the business to bertelsmann operationsedit pearson has two main streams of business global lines of business focuses on the school higher education and professional areas includes textbooks and digital technologies for teachers and students pearsons school brands include btec bug club edexcel fronter gradpoint schoolnet and successnet pearsons higher education brands include ecollege masteringmylabs revel online tutoring smarthinking and financial times publishing geographic streams focuses on north american market growth markets and core markets criticismedit concerns exist around the amount of influence pearson a commercial company has on public education other concerns are around tax avoidance the high value contracts and in one instance laying off teachers to offset the high costs of testing in  more than six out of ten pearsons shareholders voted against the chief executives pay package of £m after the company made a record loss united kingdomedit pearson owns edexcel an education and examination board edexcel has produced qualifications which link to pearson texts although edexcel also continues to endorse textbooks published by other companies libyan investment authorityedit in june  pearson plc received notification that the libyan investment authority lia founded by muammar gaddafis son saif alislam gaddafi as a sovereign fund had acquired  shares within the company via euroclear on further investigation pearson said the lia may have acquired an additional  shares resulting in a total interest of  shares at the time this represented a major holding of  within the company and the investment was worth around £ million tax avoidanceedit pearson has been criticised for using offshore tax avoidance schemes involving a host of companies at a service address in luxembourg referencesedit  a b c annual results  pdf retrieved  april    the worlds  largest book publishers  publishersweeklycom  retrieved    private equity to buy pearsons idc for  billion reuters  may  retrieved  august    a b c d e f g our history pearsoncom retrieved  april    blackwall tunnel northbound  engineering timelines  centenary of the opening of the blackwall tunnel  greenwich peninsula history the history of the greenwich peninsula in south east london  southern blackwall the blackwall tunnel survey of london volumes  and  poplar blackwall and isle of dogs  pp – accessed  march   graces guide to british industrial history weetman dickinson pearson  funding universe pearson plc history  john alfred spender  weetman pearson first viscount cowdray – p  isbn  the pearson firm took up the work of construction managers in october   history of pearson plc – fundinguniverse retrieved  march    the sennar dam and t